## Branching
---Released to production is the master branch. Create another branch  for test and development
---Create branch as per the following command:
git branch dev

--- green colour and asterics marks shows , currently we are in this branch 
--displays all branches in your local repository
git branch 

--- come out of the current branch
git checkout <branch name>
git checkout dev

-- to check which branch we are currently working
git branch
git status

---move to master branch
git checkout master

#### merge
--check the difference in two locations
git diff master..dev

--merge
git merge <branch name>
git merge dev
git merge --no-ff dev

#### Clean Up
--delete a branch from local repository
git branch -d <branch name>
git branch -d dev

-- delete a branch from remote repository
git push [remote project] -delete [branch name]



